import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    for series in data['Series'].unique():
        series_data = data[data['Series'] == series]
        ax.scatter(series_data['X'], series_data['Y'], label=series)
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the correlation between X and Y for each series?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column=['X', 'Y'], by='Series', ax=ax)
    plt.title('What is the mean and standard deviation of X and Y for each series?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(10, 10))
    axs = axs.flatten()
    for i, series in enumerate(data['Series'].unique()):
        axs[i].hist(data[data['Series'] == series]['X'], alpha=0.5, label='X')
        axs[i].hist(data[data['Series'] == series]['Y'], alpha=0.5, label='Y')
        axs[i].set_title(f'Series {series}')
        axs[i].legend(loc='upper right')
    fig.suptitle('What is the distribution of X and Y for each series?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    series = data['Series'].unique()
    colors = ['red', 'green', 'blue', 'orange']
    for i, s in enumerate(series):
        df = data[data['Series'] == s]
        ax.scatter(df['X'], df['Y'], color=colors[i], label=s)
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the relationship between X and Y across all series?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    series = data['Series'].unique()
    colors = ['red', 'blue', 'green', 'purple']
    for i, s in enumerate(series):
        df = data[data['Series'] == s]
        ax.plot(df['X'], df['Y'], marker='o', linestyle='', color=colors[i], label=s)
        ax.plot(df['X'], df['Y'], linestyle='-', color=colors[i])
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the difference between the four series?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
